@seefs001 It's related to fiber core.
```
func Test_App_MethodNotAllowed(t *testing.T) {
	app := New()
	app.Use(func(ctx *Ctx) {
		ctx.Next()
	})
	// ...
}
```
Add any middleware will failed the `Test_App_MethodNotAllowed`.

Thanks for providing good information regarding this bug report @Aoi-hosizora, I can confirm that this is related to the Fiber core router. I will investigate and keep you updated üëç 

PS: Both [Recover()](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/blob/master/middleware/recover.md) & [Logger()](https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/blob/master/middleware/logger.md) are now part of the Fiber middleware core.
```go
import (
  "github.com/gofiber/fiber"
  "github.com/gofiber/fiber/middleware"
)

func main() {
  // ...

  app.Use(middleware.Recover())
  app.Use(middleware.Logger())

  // ...
}
```

@Fenny Oh yeah, response code is 405 now, but middleware still outputs 404 (`c.Fasthttp.Response.StatusCode()`).

```go
func main() {
	app := fiber.New()
	app.Use(logger.New())
	app.Use(func(c *fiber.Ctx) {
		c.Next()
		log.Println(c.Fasthttp.Response.StatusCode())
	})
	app.Get("/a", func(c *fiber.Ctx) {})
	_ = app.Listen(2333)
}
```

